/*
 * SmartEdge — English (base) localization
 *
 * Format: "key" = "value";
 *
 * SwiftUI Text("Foo") looks up "Foo" in this file at runtime and falls
 * back to the literal if the key is missing. We keep the English string
 * as both the key AND the value for the base locale so adding a new
 * Korean translation only requires editing ko.lproj/Localizable.strings.
 *
 * Why explicit strings file: this app is going to ship to Korean
 * speakers as the primary audience; relying on Xcode-extracted
 * .xcstrings would tie localization to Xcode 15+ which works against
 * the macOS 13 deployment target.
 */

